text: This time last year I found myself wanting to change my career path. I told myself ‚ÄúI never want to work for money again, but only because I enjoy the work I do‚Äù. I modeled Lester Brown‚Äôs spirit of absolute certainty and among at least hundreds of other applicants I got the position that would change my life and begin the path to fulfilling my own destiny. It has always been my dream to become an artist, and for the last 10 years, I‚Äôve been wanting to become an animator. I no longer have to wake up dreading the next few hours to come. Now I wake up and get ready to have fun! Now I draw animated characters for a living and the company is paying for me to go to school and get my bachelors in animation! I believe listening to this video about 3x a day for at least a week before my interviews helped get me in the right mindset to prove I am the only candidate for the Sketch Artist position. I am so blessed and lucky, but before all that, I had to believe I was worth it. I had to look at the Fatalist in the mirror and say ‚ÄúI am worthy of happiness, and I deserve to realize my purpose in life.‚Äù Then the man in the mirror smiled back at me. Every step thereafter has counted towards my dreams.Ôªø

text: Some people think they have to put things on hold when you have a child, but infants, toddlers and really young children love to learn and stay busy! Do what you like and involve them they will love it! If you garden, paint, play musical instruments, cooking/baking, exercising , sewing heck they will even clean with you! Put on some music , not too loud, and have a positive attitude and dont expect too much perfection and just have fun!! If you like photography teach your child to take photos right along your side if you park them in front of the TV then that is what they will be used to and wont want to turn it off they start living in a fantasy world! Same with internet! Avoid it as much as possible!! Dont ask your child too many questions about the future especially their adult life- it creates anxiety! Put your infant right next to you in a safe area and involve them while you do things you enjoy! They will learn to be productive too as they grow! Some of my daughters best memories are of us gardening flowers and vegetables , her first shoes were tiny garden boots.Ôªø

text:
Well, I'll be 60 next week (don't know how THAT happened!!!), and I can tell you that nothing will change until YOU do.

I got so caught up in the day to day that I didn't even REALIZE other options existed until about 20 years ago. I had started waking up when I became mother to my grandson and changed my focus. Now that he's older, there are so many things that fascinate me that I can't choose one to start with! 

I've found that the MOST important thing is to know, love and accept YOURSELF.  Once you accomplish that, everything else will fall into place. It requires effort - as does everything worth doing - but it's worth it. 

I have a large library of books (PDFs) that can help with this.  Anyone interested can contact me thru my channel. It to that  take me a week or more to respond, but I will get back to you.

Don't piss away most of your life like I did.Ôªø

text: My wife and kids life has gotten turned upside down last year. We had found out that my wife has stage 4 brest cancer and it's spread to her lymph nodes.  She has had a numerous amount of surgeries and has been fighting for her life . It has left me with our 4 children 12, 7, 2, 1 . It's very hard and things have changed so fast. I'm lost and don't know what to do . I want to be more than what I am and do more than what I'm doing but insurance is declining everything and if I work her insurance will be canceled. So I'm working under the table but that isn't good for long term retirement,  social security  etc... her memory is bad , neurological issues , neuropathy and that's to list few. I feel stuck and all I want is to be the best I can be for my children and for my beautiful wife to be around for her children and watch them grow , graduate,  get married,  have kids, and the things  every mother and parent should experience. I'm lost.....so lost. She's in another state getting treatment while I'm in another working under the tale trying to make things work. Pay bills and be here for everything and everyone.  We have been together since we were 16 and wanted to start a family and we did that's what our DREAM was... and to have this happen we all feel cheated. Why? I don't understand. ...? We are not bad people and we obided by everything we we're supposed to. Why? It's like I'm stuck and don't know what to do. I look at my kids and I just want them to be good people . And I'm afraid that everything that's going on is going to affect them and I feel ad they are being subjected to this and it's not their fault. I am an emotional wreck. Anyways enough of my ranting and emotional situation.Ôªø

text:
Hay iv chosen to start sharing my story with anyone that can take value from it, I can see great value in your message so don‚Äôt want to just promote myself to your followers but would like to ad some value and invite people to join me on my journey of a self-improvement movement...



I Grew up on a council estate the oldest of 6 children with 6 different dads, our mum is an alcoholic and the home was filled with a lot of drink and violence... 

We never had much food in the house and I suffered extreme racism from the local community, as I was the only mixed-race face in school.


People told me I was ugly and would never get a girlfriend...


Everyone took the piss and doubted me for wanting to become a singer...


I left school at 16 with a criminal record and couldn't even spell my own name, I was angry, lost and confused.

I ended up drinking too much, having a breakdown, suffering from anxiety and depression and almost ended up in jail by the age of 21...


I ended up in debt and had to claim benefits to survive. It's been an incredible rollercoaster of a journey...


I'm now 37 have a beautiful home, have a beautiful wife and 2 awesome little dogs that I love more than words can describe :-) 

I tour as an international singing artist with my wife...

I work as a music agent and become friends with artists that I used to buy the records of...

I was the best recruit on an ITV show called Bad Lads Army...


I get to travel to places and do the things I used to only dream of, and I'm now on a journey to share my story with the world to help other people to believe that it is possible and things can change. You can create a world you design! 


Marcus @ReshapeTheStars  YouTube:

author: All Might

text:
I came to realize who were  toxic people in my life(one of them being me myself) who dragged me down when i met this guy who became my best friend even tho i never actually told him that. He was the only inspiration i ever had in my life, not my mom, siblings, famous people, in my head nobody was worthy enough, nobody that i can look up to.... for the first time in life i knew in what direction i want to go, everything that friend did on daily basis was like an eureka to me, he thought me so much about life without even realizing it. I admired him so much i wanted to be just like him. He was the real life version of my vision what kind of person i wanted to be.  And one day... i got the news that he killed himself... i was so confused why, i still am. What he did that day raised so many questions about life in general, and i just got tired of living life, just stopped caring about anyone or anything. I lost everything that day... I don't hate him for that, everything he did in life had some kind of purpose. Later i learned how fucked up his childhood was that probably led to that decision, he suffered from depression and i had no clue cause that man was the definition of happiness.... At least  that's what he allowed us to see. 

And now 3 years latter... im still sitting in this damn uncomfortable chair feeling lost, without a job, fucked up my collage education i stopped going out of the house, got chronically ill and i still don't care cause i feel unworthy just like all the years before i met this friend. Browsing my life away on the internet trying to motivate myself again... in hopes somebody or something will kindle the fire in me. I get myself moving for a few days a month, but that quickly falls apart cause i cant deal with my head and stay consistent at anything. So what i started doing is listening to these speeches as much as i can to burn it into my brain. To force myself to say yes to goals i was once 'hungry' for.  Talking to people became my worst fear, cause i cant really explain my thought process without being judged so im writing this here just to get it out... have a happy and productive decade people.Ôªø

My fear friends. This is a great video full of useful info. Think of all of the inventions that have come to man's mind and then see that single thought

Is it the Nuclear Bomb that has such a destructive force that it could kill EVERY living thing on Our world? 
The answer is "No". You'll laugh
When I tell you that one of the most DESTRUCTIVE objects in YOUR life
is in nearly everyone's house and it's NOT powered by electricity. What is it? 
It's the MIRROR in your bedroom, bathroom, hall and wherever. 
When we look at our reflection,
We instantly JUDGE ourselves on our appearances. The mirror tells us that
We're attractive, ugly, young, old, fat, thin, and by your OWN JUDGEMENTof self, YOU either like or hate what you see. YOUR mirror, without saying a word, tells you that you ARE better     looking than others but, NOT as good looking as YOUR idol. Imagine a world without mirrors. What a different world it would be if you couldn't see your OWN reflection. Without the mirror, you would NEVER see yourself and thereby, you would have NOTHING to Compare yourself with. There would be NO competition to look better than others  as no one else Would ever know what they looked like either !  What's the meaning of this rant then?  Simple.
DON'T look into your mirror for self appraisal, Cos if you're totally HONEST
with yourself, you may see self - condemnation staring back at you.
YOU ARE NOT that reflection, YOU are
A child of the Universe, a Spiritual Being that exits and extends beyond time and space, so, STOP JUDGING YOURSELF AND OTHERS BY THEIR OUTWARD APPEARANCES ! 
Some of the Most Beautiful SPIRITUAL
People you have met have looked,  OUTWARDLY, like the biggest bag of garbage you've ever seen, but, INWARDLY, they are full of Wisdom, Empathy and have unlimited  Compassion and Unconditional love  for their fellow creatures. author: V Velas

text:
Hey Milo, 

I don't think I have ever replied to anyone on YouTube, but when I read your comment, I kind of felt compelled to respond.  I was also on your boat.  When I was 28/29 years old, I started thinking about going back to school too.  I was working in commercial insurance for about 6 years after undergrad and I absolutely just hated what I did for a living.  It was scary to think that heading into my 30's that I had absolutely no idea what I was doing with my life.  It was scary to think of starting all over again, especially when my friends around me were getting married/having kids/buying houses.  But you know, everyone has their own roads, and everyone figures things out at their own time.  Anyway, long story short, I decided to take the leap and I started working on my prerequisite courses (which took me about 2 years) before actually getting into grad school for physical therapy.  I'm 35 now too and I have about a year and a half left before I graduate, and my program is a 3-4 year program at $100,000, not to mention living expenses.  It's a lot of money.  It's a big decision, definitely weigh out your pros and cons.  I guess what I am trying to say is if you are not currently happy with what you are doing and you are certain that you want to become a dental hygienist, I figure it's worth it to be doing something that you love.  I am not saying that the road is going to be easy.  It has definitely been a roller coaster of emotions these last couple of years with this career change, but at the end of the day, I have absolutely no regrets.  Just thought I'd share my story.  Good luck to you brother!Ôªø

text: I'm not gonna lie, at first i was when i saw there was no morgan freeman, i was pissed of man. I was just a little bit in my head like "if you don't gettt shit shittt atta here." So at that point i realized, okay, obvious click bait, but then i started hearing speeches, that outright just changed my life. Motivational pieces are a dime a dozen okay, they all usually sound the same to a certain extent with slight variation, or different perspectives on already looked upon topics. But man, when that man spoke, there was something different. There was having had the hard times, there was his own self transition as well, but he made me laugh like never before. It was like combining a good black comedian, that rocky feel where you go from nothing to something but more intense, but some how still exuding this unbelievably positive outlook on life, truly vibrant energy that overwhelms you. So i just have to be the first one to say, I have got to thank you for your personal use of clickbait, because it lead me to something so powerful and life changing, that i may not have necessarily clicked with a different thumbnail. Besides, 10 times a day you click on a random clip not even looking at the title just to see some tits or some half clothes wearing woman to draw attention, i think this is using thumbnails for a good purpose for once.Ôªø

text: There are so many truizums in what Les is saying. But, this is only a good message when there is even a sliver of light.  I have not that sliver. I am old at only 55 years old. I was in an auto accident 9 years ago,  but have worked with passion to ensure my wife and three children would have the best life i could provide. But the daily pain got to be too much and my boss sacked me. Now I'm maxed out on credit cards,  overdrawn in my bank accounts. I was wanr to work from home as an affiliate marketer, but I do not have the knowledge. Besides,  my wife is very traditional and wants me to get back to a 9-5 job. My children see are on their own for the most part so what do I have to drive me.  Yes,  that's right... Nothing! So, I if you can and you see in even a sliver of light,  do what ever you can to push through the struggles.  But for me,  I need help to get my family my life insurance. text: Realize you posted this 3 months ago but maybe you will get this.  I took a course by Jose Silva through which I learned a technique to abate negative thoughts...." cancel cancel". No kidding...... when you start an internal conversation that is dark, cut yourself off and say cancel cancel. It will stop. When it starts again....cancel cancel. I added to this.......putting positive scenerios in my head when the darkness was being stubborn. Also. you can keep a written list of positive  "happy"things ....your pet,a song, the trees, the feeling of jello....doesn't have to be big. just a list you can recite to yourself if the thoughts are being stubborn, look at the list and recite it , even if in your mind. I've found this extremely helpful, we're all different but it may work for you. All Best!Ôªø

text: Something brought me to this today. I am great full it did.. I am 56 years old, currently unemployed, and for each day that passes I find myself losing more and more of my confidence and desire of accomplishing more in my life. I know with every bit of me that there is more for me to experience and accomplish in my life, that this is not all there is, in have so much more to offer in  this world. But my "Fear" seems to consume me more and more each day that passes, and that conversation going on inside has taken control each time.  My daughter said to me one day " Mom, what happened to the way you use to be?" "You would never doubt yourself like you do these days". I don't have an answer for her. Hearing this today is a definite blessing, one that has allowed me to experience that empowering feeling I would get when i knew there was nothing that could stop me from achieving whatever I wanted, a feeling I have not felt in several years now. I don't know who I am  today.. But I'm gonna make this my decade and find out! Thanks Les, your words are amazing, I would love to have the opportunity to see and hear you in person one day.Ôªø

text:
I have a little library of motivational Youtube videos that I listen to in MP3 format.  I had a bigger one, but I had to delete the ones with Gary Vaynerchuk. In my opinion, to use the F-bomb as an exclamation point to the degree he does crosses the line from motivational to crass.  It's a shame, because although he has good stuff to say, the F-bombs take away from it and are unnecessary.
I know he thinks he's being "real," but to me, he's being lazy and avoiding the hard work of crafting a message that gets peoples' attention by how well it's spoken, rather than get their attention through cheap shock value.
Listen to Les Brown, and you'll see what I mean by "crafting a message."Ôªø
